110
00:07:30,131 --> 00:07:30,311
So,

111
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:36,846
For me, at least, I think my relationships are way more important than the money.

112
00:07:37,447 --> 00:07:39,527
So, the relationships are...

113
00:07:40,328 --> 00:07:43,849
Sorry, the money serves the relationships, the relationships do not serve the money.

114
00:07:45,401 --> 00:07:51,503
And what this can mean practically is that I try not to talk about money in the first meeting with an indie.

115
00:07:52,724 --> 00:08:00,107
So often they're coming to me, and they're not audio experts, and they want to get an understanding of what that would mean,

116
00:08:00,307 --> 00:08:06,129
and they're kind of looking for a number, and when you give them that number, or when I give them that number, the conversation tends to end.

117
00:08:07,178 --> 00:08:11,242
And, you know, because then they're going to need to make their decision about which

118
00:08:11,362 --> 00:08:12,583
person to use for the audio.

119
00:08:13,044 --> 00:08:15,627
Now, I'm not saying you should be evasive about talking about money.

120
00:08:16,187 --> 00:08:20,892
I'm just saying that it's great to build an understanding of the client, the project,

121
00:08:21,253 --> 00:08:25,898
and their expectations of what they want from the audio before you get into that money conversation.

122
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:29,857
And I like to approach that by kind of working backwards

123
00:08:29,897 --> 00:08:32,059
from what's their sort of audio budget,

124
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,562
what's the scope of the game, and then coming up

125
00:08:34,602 --> 00:08:36,764
with something that's really appropriate for their project,

126
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:38,526
maybe giving them a few options.

127
00:08:39,106 --> 00:08:42,710
And they come away happy having increased understanding.

128
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:44,451
You've built up that relationship.

129
00:08:44,932 --> 00:08:46,673
So even if it doesn't work out with them,

130
00:08:47,214 --> 00:08:48,415
you've built up the relationship.

131
00:08:48,435 --> 00:08:49,176
And that's always helpful.

132
00:08:50,635 --> 00:08:54,497
