00:11:01,824 --> 00:11:04,465
You're operating holistically in the prototyping phase.

170
00:11:04,505 --> 00:11:06,866
So when they're kind of figuring out what the game is,

171
00:11:07,626 --> 00:11:08,826
support them with the audio.

172
00:11:08,866 --> 00:11:12,368
So they're sort of iterating using all of the disciplines.

173
00:11:13,928 --> 00:11:14,508
Communication.

174
00:11:15,108 --> 00:11:18,389
Communication is key, absolutely key,

175
00:11:18,449 --> 00:11:21,290
especially when you have an indie team

176
00:11:22,231 --> 00:11:23,931
and you're scattered across the globe.

177
00:11:25,592 --> 00:11:27,252
For example, with.

178
00:11:28,325 --> 00:11:30,945
Yoku's Island Express, we had weekly Skype calls.

179
00:11:32,986 --> 00:11:38,187
That seemed very doable when the game was supposed to be one year long.

180
00:11:39,228 --> 00:11:43,269
The game went on for three years, though, which meant that every single week for three

