00:11:58,441 --> 00:12:03,203
We made sure that we used a Google tracking sheet for things.

185
00:12:03,483 --> 00:12:11,606
I recommend you use something like Google because emailing Excel documents back and

186
00:12:11,646 --> 00:12:14,707
forth or putting an Excel doc on something like Dropbox,

187
00:12:15,127 --> 00:12:17,108
they get out of sync very easily even.

188
00:12:18,309 --> 00:12:22,489
Even using something like Perforce or any source control software,

189
00:12:22,569 --> 00:12:24,870
it is possible for your documents to get out of sync.

190
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:30,231
And then somebody makes change and now you've got two versions of something floating around.

191
00:12:30,711 --> 00:12:36,992
And with documentation and communication, two versions of something can be really detrimental.

192
00:12:37,112 --> 00:12:41,653
So we made sure we had this document that tracked all of our goals, obstacles, and progress.

193
00:12:41,693 --> 00:12:46,073
